1) Create Domain group with the following input
     - Group Name
     - Group Scope (Domain Local, Global, Universal)
     - Description:
          - when the group is created
          - who request to create 
          - the manager that approval the creation

2) Create Domain user with the following input
     - First Name
     - Last Name
     - A list of groups where the user belong to
     - Name (account name)
     - Password 
     - User Cannot change password set to false
     - User Must change password when first login set to true
     - Account expiry set to Never 
     - Description
          - when the group is created
          - who request to create 
          - the manager that approval the creation

The playbook logic will as below
1) Only create group if it do not exist
2) Create user if the user do not exist and the groups assigned to the user must all exist


